# Release signing — COPY this file to `keystore.properties` (gitignored) and fill it in, OR set the
# KNIT_SIGNING_STORE_FILE / _STORE_PASSWORD / _KEY_ALIAS / _KEY_PASSWORD env vars instead (CI; the older
# KNIT_UPLOAD_* names still work). If neither is present, `assembleRelease` builds UNSIGNED (which is
# fine for exercising R8, and is exactly what F-Droid's buildserver wants). NEVER commit the real
# keystore.properties or the .jks/.keystore file.
#
# There are TWO signing identities, and they are deliberately separate keys. The build only ever sees one
# set of credentials at a time — the signingConfig below is credential-generic, so you pick the identity by
# pointing storeFile/keyAlias at the right keystore for the artifact you are cutting:
#
#   1. Play upload key  (knit-upload.jks) — for `bundleRelease` -> the AAB uploaded to Google Play.
#      This is only an *upload* key: Play App Signing re-signs with a key Google holds and we do not have,
#      so an APK we build can never carry the signature a Play-installed Knit has.
#
#   2. Distribution key (knit-dist.jks)   — for `assembleRelease` -> the universal APK published on GitHub
#      Releases and verified/redistributed by F-Droid. Its certificate SHA-256 is pinned publicly in
#      fdroiddata as `AllowedAPKSigningKeys`, so this key is effectively permanent: rotating it forces
#      every off-Play user to uninstall and reinstall. Guard it accordingly.
#
# Because F-Droid redistributes *our* APK (Binaries: + AllowedAPKSigningKeys), one distribution-key-signed
# APK serves GitHub Releases, F-Droid, direct sideload, AND Knit's own offline app-share — so a phone that
# received Knit over the mesh can still take an in-place update from F-Droid. See
# .agents/context/distribution.md.
#
# Generate a keystore (RSA 2048, 10000-day validity), then reference it below:
#   keytool -genkeypair -v -keystore knit-dist.jks -alias knit-dist \
#           -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000
#
# Print the certificate SHA-256 to paste into fdroiddata's AllowedAPKSigningKeys (lowercase, no colons):
#   keytool -list -v -keystore knit-dist.jks -alias knit-dist \
#     | awk '/SHA256:/ {gsub(/:/,"",$2); print tolower($2)}'
#
# storeFile may be absolute or relative to the repo root.
storeFile=knit-dist.jks
storePassword=CHANGE_ME
keyAlias=knit-dist
keyPassword=CHANGE_ME
